[size=4][u]Safe Cheat Panel[/u][/size]

A UI-based cheat panel accessible from the left sidebar in the map menu. Provides tools to edit player stats, inventory, research, blueprints, faction relations, galaxy exploration state, spawning capabilities, object destruction, and ship crew promotion - all through a clean, tab-based interface.

[b]Warning[/b]: Spawning unusual objects (such as multiple Player HQs) can corrupt saves. Use responsibly.

[size=3][u][b]Important Notice[/b][/u][/size]

[i]Idea Author[/i] made decision to leave the community and removed the original Cheat UI mod. Taking in account his decision to remove all his stuff from the Nexus Mods, I decided to do all my best to replace his part in the latest version of Cheat UI maintained by me and create a new mod called Safe Cheat Panel.

The new mod currently not contains the "development mode" features as I focused on the "safe" features first, but I plan to add them in the future.

Take in account: id of the mod and folder is changed to `safe_cheat_panel`.

[size=3][u][b]Features[/b][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] [b]Player Tab[/b]: Set player money and add spacesuit upgrades and ammo.
[*] [b]Inventory Tab[/b]: Edit player inventory wares across multiple categories.
[*] [b]Research Tab[/b]: Unlock or lock research individually, with full dependency handling.
[*] [b]Blueprints Tab[/b]: Unlock blueprints individually, by subcategory, or all at once.
[*] [b]Factions Tab[/b]: Edit faction relations with the player and between non-player factions.
[*] [b]Galaxy/Sectors Tab[/b]: Reveal sectors on the map at three levels of detail, or reveal all at once.
[*] [b]Spawner Tab[/b]: Spawn stations, ships (with loadout and crew options), and deployable objects.
[*] [b]Destroy Object Tab[/b]: Destroy any destructible map object, selected via the right-click context menu, with a confirmation checkbox before the button arms.
[*] [b]Promote Crew Tab[/b]: Set a player ship's Pilot/Captain, Marines, and Service Crew skill levels via star sliders, with an option to set every skill (not just the role-relevant ones) to the chosen level.
[*] [b]Right-click context menu[/b]: Spawn station, fix station, spawn ships, spawn objects, force station build completion (current and all faction stations), restock station and station build storage (current and all faction stations), teleport ship, teleport player, reveal all stations in sector, destroy object, promote crew.
[*] [b]Two modes[/b]: [b]Normal[/b] (player-owned spawns only) and [b]Extended[/b] (NPC-faction-owned spawns, additional faction options) - switchable via Extension Options.
[*] [b]Compatible with X4 8.00 and 9.00[/b].
[*] [b]Can work with SWI[/b] - please use with the [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/x4foundations/mods/2134]kuertee UI Extensions and HUD for SW Interworlds adoption mod[/url].
[/list]
