[size=3][u][b]Usage[/b][/u][/size]

Open the map and click the [b]Safe Cheat Panel[/b] icon in the left sidebar to open the panel.

[size=3][u][i]Player Tab[/i][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Set player money (0 - 1 quadrillion).
[*] Add spacesuit upgrades.
[*] Add spacesuit ammo (0 - 10,000).
[/list]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/spacesuit_upgrades.png[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Inventory Tab[/i][/u][/size]

Edit player inventory wares. Items are grouped by category - select a category from the dropdown to view and edit amounts (0 - 10,000).

Categories: Inventory, Modification Parts, Seminars, Curiosities, Luxury Items, and Mission-Only Items.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/inventory.png[/img]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/modification_parts.png[/img]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/seminars.png[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Research Tab[/i][/u][/size]

Shows all available research, more or less hierarchically. Research can be unlocked or locked individually with full dependency handling:
[list]
[*] Unlocking a research item unlocks all of its prerequisites automatically.
[*] Locking a research item locks all research that depends on it.
[*] An [b]Unlock All[/b] button is available at the top of the tab.
[/list]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/research_tab.png[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Blueprints Tab[/i][/u][/size]

Browse and unlock blueprints by category and subcategory, or unlock all at once. Individual items can be unlocked within any subcategory. There is no option to lock back blueprints once unlocked.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/blueprints_start.png[/img]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/blueprints_all_partly_expanded.png[/img]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/blueprints_modules_all.png[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Factions Tab[/i][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Edit faction relations with the player (-30 to +30, mapped to actual internal values).
[*] Edit relations between non-player factions (available in extended mode).
[*] Factions become available as they are discovered in-game.
[*] Locked relations are shown as read-only.
[/list]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/factions_and_relations.png[/img]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/factions_and_relations_non_player.png[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Galaxy/Sectors Tab[/i][/u][/size]

Reveal sectors on the map at three levels of detail:
[list]
[*] [b]Level 1[/b]: Reveal sector position only.
[*] [b]Level 2[/b]: Reveal the path to the sector from the player (or from the nearest known sector if the target is not directly reachable).
[*] [b]Level 3[/b]: Reveal all gates and super highways within the sector.
[/list]
A [b]Reveal All[/b] button reveals every sector at all levels at once.

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/sectors.png[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Spawner Tab[/i][/u][/size]

[size=3][u]Ship Spawner[/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Select a ship to spawn.
[*] Select a loadout (game defaults: Low/Medium/High, or player-defined loadouts).
[*] Select the owning faction (player only in normal mode; any faction in extended mode).
[*] Select the crew race (all races available; Kha'ak, Xenon and Drones are not recommended).
[*] Set the number of ships per row (up to 10) and the number of rows (up to 10).
[/list]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/loadout_selection.png[/img]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/loadout_result.png[/img][img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/loadout_result_part_2.png[/img]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/crew_race_selection.png[/img]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/crew_result.png[/img]

[size=3][u]Station Spawner[/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Select a construction plan (player-created plans, or pre-defined plans in extended mode).
[*] Select the owning faction (player only in normal mode; any faction in extended mode).
[/list]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/station_spawner.png[/img]

[size=3][u]Object Spawner[/u][/size]
[list]
[*] Select a deployable object to spawn.
[*] Set the number per row (up to 10), number of rows (up to 10), and spacing between objects (up to 100 km).
[/list]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/object_spawner.png[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Destroy Object Tab[/i][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] The target object can only be set via the [b]Destroy Object[/b] right-click context menu action, which is only offered while this tab is open.
[*] Shows the selected object's name, ID code, and sector.
[*] A confirmation checkbox must be ticked before the [b]Destroy[/b] button becomes active.
[*] The player's own currently-piloted ship, gates, highway entry/exit gates, and super highways cannot be targeted.
[*] The object is removed instantly, without an explosion.
[/list]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/object_destroy.png[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Promote Crew Tab[/i][/u][/size]
[list]
[*] The target ship can only be set via the [b]Promote Crew[/b] right-click context menu action (player-owned ships only), which is only offered while this tab is open.
[*] Set the Pilot/Captain, Marines, and Service Crew skill levels independently via 1-5 star sliders; each label shows the category's current average.
[*] By default, only the skill(s) relevant to the role are set exactly to the chosen level, while the remaining skills are scaled proportionally to their current values.
[*] An optional checkbox sets [b]every[/b] skill (not just the role-relevant ones) to the chosen level instead.
[*] [b]Cancel[/b] clears the selected ship and any pending changes; [b]Reset[/b] reverts pending slider changes without deselecting the ship; [b]Apply[/b] commits the changes.
[/list]
[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/promote_crew.png[/img]

[size=3][u][i]Right-click Context Menu on Map[/i][/u][/size]

Right-clicking on the map gives access to the following actions, depending on the current panel mode and active tab:
[list]
[*] [b]Spawn Station[/b]: Spawns a station at the clicked position using the current Spawner tab settings.
[*] [b]Fix Station[/b]: Appears only on stations that are missing control entities (defence officer or engineer). Initialises the station correctly.
[*] [b]Reveal Stations in Sector[/b]: Reveals all stations in the sector of the clicked position on the map, including their names and positions.
[*] [b]Spawn Ships[/b]: Spawns ships at the clicked position using the current Spawner tab settings.
[*] [b]Spawn Objects[/b]: Spawns deployable objects at the clicked position using the current Spawner tab settings.
[*] [b]Force Build Completion: Current Station[/b]: Instantly completes the construction of a station that is currently building, by finishing all build tasks and spawning all missing modules and sub-entities. Appears only on stations that are currently under construction. [i]In[/i] [b]extended[/b] [i]mode available for non-player faction stations[/i].
[*] [b]Force Build Completion: All Faction Stations[/b]: Instantly completes the construction of all stations belonging to the same faction, by finishing all build tasks and spawning all missing modules and sub-entities. Appears only on stations that are currently under construction. [i]Only available in[/i] [b]extended[/b] [i]mode, as for player as for non-player faction stations[/i].
[*] [b]Restock: Current Station[/b]: Instantly restocks the current station with all required resources. Appears only on stations that are currently under construction. Takes into account the trade offers and ware reservation. [i]In[/i] [b]extended[/b] [i]mode available for non-player faction stations[/i].
[*] [b]Restock: All Faction Stations[/b]: Instantly restocks all stations belonging to the same faction with all required resources. Appears only on stations that are currently under construction. Takes into account the trade offers and ware reservation. [i]Only available in[/i] [b]extended[/b] [i]mode, as for player as for non-player faction stations[/i].
[*] [b]Restock: Current Build Storage[/b]: Instantly restocks the current station's build storage with all required resources. Appears only on stations that are currently under construction. Takes into account the trade offers and ware reservation. [i]In[/i] [b]extended[/b] [i]mode available for non-player faction stations[/i].
[*] [b]Restock: All Faction Build Storages[/b]: Instantly restocks all stations belonging to the same faction with all required resources in their build storages. Appears only on stations that are currently under construction. Takes into account the trade offers and ware reservation. [i]Only available in[/i] [b]extended[/b] [i]mode, as for player as for non-player faction stations[/i].
[*] [b]Teleport Here[/b]: Teleports the player's currently piloted ship to the clicked position.
[*] [b]Teleport To[/b]: Teleports the player character to the clicked object or position.
[*] [b]Destroy Object[/b]: Sets the clicked object as the target on the Destroy Object tab. Only offered while that tab is open. The player's own currently-piloted ship, gates, highway entry/exit gates, and super highways cannot be targeted.
[*] [b]Promote Crew[/b]: Sets the clicked ship as the target on the Promote Crew tab. Only offered while that tab is open, and only for player-owned ships.
[/list]
[size=3][u][i]Extension Options[/i][/u][/size]

An options menu is available via [b]Options Menu > Extension options > Safe Cheat Panel[/b].

[img]https://raw.githubusercontent.com/chemodun/X4-SafeCheatPanel/refs/heads/main/docs/images/extension_options.png[/img]

There you can switch between [b]Normal[/b] and [b]Extended[/b] modes, which determines the availability of certain features as described in the features section. You can also enable or disable debug logging.

Debug logging can be enabled to write detailed information about the mod's operations to the X4 log file, which is useful for troubleshooting.

